# Shotcut local macOS (Homebrew) build

Repo path: `~/development/shotcut`. Fork: `hashir-ayaz/shotcut`. Upstream remote: `upstream`.

## How to build and run

```bash
cmake -GNinja -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \
  -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH="/opt/homebrew/opt/qt;/opt/homebrew" \
  -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX="$HOME/development/shotcut/install" \
  -S . -B build
cmake --build build -j"$(sysctl -n hw.ncpu)"
cmake --install build
./run.sh   # REQUIRED after every install
```

Launch with `./run.sh` or `open install/Shotcut.app`. Full notes: `LOCAL_SETUP.md`.

## Never forget: Homebrew MLT paths

Homebrew uses `$(brew --prefix mlt)/lib/mlt` and `.../share/mlt`, **not** `mlt-7`. Wrong paths cause:

- `mlt_repository_init: no plugins found in "/opt/homebrew/lib/mlt-7"`
- Failed to open media / error saving projects

`run.sh` sets `MLT_REPOSITORY`, `MLT_DATA`, `MLT_PROFILES_PATH`, `FREI0R_PATH`, bundles CuteLogger, and wraps the app binary as `Shotcut` → `Shotcut.bin`. After `cmake --install`, always run `./run.sh` once to restore the wrapper.

Do not “fix” media/save bugs by changing Shotcut C++ until the log is checked for missing MLT plugins.
